  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - By reason of its design, scale, massing and siting it is considered that the proposed additions to the properties would appear overly dominant, would fail to maintain subservience to the existing property and would disrupt the established rear building line of the group of 6 terraced properties in which the application property is a part, resulting in an incongruous form of development that would cause signficant harm their character and that of the wider area, contrary to Local Plan Policies LP1 and LP5, the Councils Housing SPD.",
    "Reason : 2 - By reason of their size, siting close to a number of neighbouring residential properties and combination of terraces at both first and second floor level, it is considered that the proposed roof terraces would create a significant sense of perceived overlooking to the rear amenity space and rear fenestration of properties to the rear which would appear overbearing, causing significant harm to neighbour amenity, contrary to Policy LP2B of the Local Plan.",
    "Reason : 3 - In dealing with this application the Council has implemented the requirement in the National Planning Policy Framework to work with the applicant in a positive and proactive manner and the Council has, as far as practicable, sought solutions to problems arising in relation to dealing with the planning application. We have made available detailed advice in the form of our statutory policies in the Local Plan consisting of the Core Strategy, Development Management Policies Document, Supplementary Planning documents and where appropriate the Site Specific Allocations Document as well as offering a full pre application advice service. However, we have been unable to seek solutions to problems as the principle of the proposal is clearly contrary to our statutory policies and negotiation could not overcome the reasons for refusal."
  ],
